    <message id="learning.modular-arithmetic.content">

        <center>
            Modular Arithmetic is probably the most important concept to get your head around when learning about
            Cryptography. It is used in every aspect. The good thing is that it isnt that difficult a topic and
            can be understood after a few examples.

            The idea is that after a certain point you wrap back to zero. A good example of this is a clock. On most modern clock faces the numbers go from 1-12. When it gets to 12 it then goes to 1 again. This is know as Mod 12 arithmetic.

        </center>

